1
00:00:01,067 --> 00:00:02,200
<i>No one has ever attacked me
like this before.</i>

2
00:00:02,333 --> 00:00:04,267
<i> This case isn't over, Marina.</i>

3
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:05,400
<i> We still have to know more</i>

4
00:00:05,533 --> 00:00:07,333
<i>about Michael and
Federico's deaths.</i>

5
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:09,433
[GRUNTS]

6
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:12,700
<i>I've done what you told me
to do, ma'am.</i>

7
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:13,967
<i> Are you sure?</i>

8
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:15,433
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

9
00:00:15,567 --> 00:00:18,067
<i>Is it because of Jade
and the mysterious earrings?</i>

10
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,133
She said we're not kids anymore.

11
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,167
<i> That a lot has changed.</i>

12
00:00:23,533 --> 00:00:24,933
<i>I know you feel at ease
around me.</i>

13
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:29,567
<i> Is this what you mean?</i>

14
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,367
<i> I know you're just passing by.</i>

15
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,033
<i>You're not really
going to work today.</i>

16
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,300
<i> Come on.</i>

17
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,667
[SIGHS]

18
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:41,233
Okay, Miss Trixie,
please wait for your keys.

19
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:42,767
- I'll just get it.
- Alright. Thank you.

20
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,200
Okay. Thank you.

21
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,367
[LUGGAGE THUDS]

22
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:49,233
- [WHEELS RATTLING]
- [LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:51,500
Ah, yes, ma'am.
Welcome to Hotel 88.

24
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:53,633
Do you have a reservation?

25
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:55,567
What? Reservation?

26
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,300
Is that necessary?

27
00:00:58,433 --> 00:00:59,700
- [RAPHIE] Yes.
- I don't have one.

28
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:03,433
But, maybe you still have
vacant rooms?

29
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:04,800
Oh.

30
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:08,000
As of now, we still have
vacant rooms, but just the--

31
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:09,167
The VIP?

32
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:11,967
- Oh, yes, ma'am.
- Oh, the VIP. That's it.

33
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,267
Give me the VIP room.

34
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:16,400
Give me the nicest, the biggest,

35
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:19,300
and the most expensive room
you have.

36
00:01:19,433 --> 00:01:20,400
[RAPHIE] Okay. Right away.

37
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:23,300
The VIP room,
our best and most expensive one.

38
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:24,867
- That's it, I like
- It'll be yours, ma'am.

39
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,133
Alright.

40
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:28,367
- Are my keys ready?
- Ah, yes, ma'am.

41
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,900
- Here, ma'am.
- Thank you.

42
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:31,000
This is also a VIP room,
isn't it?

43
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,600
Oh, yes.

44
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:33,833
- Thank you.
- Thank you, ma'am.

45
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,100
This way.

46
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:37,100
- Enjoy!
- [WHEELS RATTLING]

47
00:01:37,233 --> 00:01:39,833
Okay. Let's process
your VIP room, ma'am.

48
00:01:39,967 --> 00:01:41,367
What are you talking about?

49
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:43,300
No. Put it on my brother's tab.

50
00:01:43,433 --> 00:01:44,733
Just a regular room
for me, please.

51
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:45,533
But you said--

52
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:47,833
I said a regular room. Zip it.

53
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:49,800
Alright.

54
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:52,233
I'm just going
to re-process it...

55
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:53,300
Do you need help?

56
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:54,533
- No, it's fine.
- I can write it myself.

57
00:01:54,667 --> 00:01:56,567
I can do it, ma'am.
Thank you.

58
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,533
Thank you.

59
00:01:57,667 --> 00:02:02,000
[LIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:02:04,367 --> 00:02:11,333
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:06,100
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]
- Oh, Miss,

62
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:08,233
have you seen Luna?

63
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:09,900
I don't know
where she is, ma'am.

64
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,000
Okay, thank you.

65
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:16,067
[KIKO] Jade!

66
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,900
- Jade.
- What now?

67
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,033
Jade, hold on.

68
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,067
I wouldn't bother you
if it's not important to me.

69
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,500
I'm busy.

70
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:26,133
Jade, just one minute, please!

71
00:03:26,267 --> 00:03:27,400
Okay, five seconds. Five.

72
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:28,800
- Yesterday, you asked
- Four.

73
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:30,700
- if I know something.
- Three. Two.

74
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,800
- What is it that I don't know?
- One. Time's up!

75
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:33,900
Jade, please!

76
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:38,033
That was nothing.

77
00:03:39,067 --> 00:03:39,933
Don't worry about that.

78
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:41,867
I also don't know
the things you don't know.

79
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,900
Jade, don't be like this.

80
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:44,933
You wouldn't bring it up
if it's just nothing.

81
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,100
And I won't stop, Jade.

82
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,867
We can't be like this forever.

83
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,967
Just avoiding each other.

84
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:53,100
You know there are matters
we have to talk about.

85
00:03:57,733 --> 00:03:58,600
Fine.

86
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,167
You want to know the truth?

87
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:02,233
Yes.

88
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:06,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

89
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,067
There's a restaurant downstairs.

90
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,200
There's a bar here upstairs.

91
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,067
Both are managed by Monette.

92
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,433
Noted, sir.

93
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:17,033
[GASPS] Martin!

94
00:04:17,167 --> 00:04:18,233
- [CHUCKLES]
- Trixie?

95
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:19,867
- [MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]
- How are you?

96
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,133
What are you doing here?

97
00:04:21,267 --> 00:04:22,533
Oh, of course, for you.

98
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:25,067
I felt that you needed me here,

99
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,300
so here I am.

100
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:27,400
Is she your sister, sir?

101
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:29,600
When did I make you feel that?

102
00:04:29,733 --> 00:04:31,733
- Oh, Martin--
- That's a serious question.

103
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:34,267
Aren't you happy to see me?

104
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,300
I crossed the ocean for you.

105
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:38,100
Of course. Of course I'm happy.

106
00:04:38,233 --> 00:04:39,600
That settles it.

107
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:42,133
- Hi, sissy!
- Oh!

108
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:43,200
I'm Sari!

109
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:44,867
I'm Sir Martin's assistant.

110
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,667
Just let me know
if you need anything

111
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,067
and I'll help you
with all my loving heart!

112
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,333
- [CHUCKLES]
- Yeah.

113
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:51,533
This is my assistant.

114
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:54,800
Oh... assistant.

115
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:57,100
So how long--

116
00:04:57,233 --> 00:04:58,400
Don't ask.

117
00:04:58,533 --> 00:05:00,400
Oh, okay.

118
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,467
It's nice to meet you, Sari.

119
00:05:02,633 --> 00:05:04,233
I'll introduce you
to my brothers.

120
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:05,833
Oh, great. G, let's go.

121
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:09,467
At last,
I'll finally meet your brothers.

122
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,000
Let's go?

123
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:12,100
Let's go.

124
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:14,000
- [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]
- [MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:05:14,767 --> 00:05:16,467
Jade, I'm begging you.

126
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:21,900
It's...

127
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,167
about the earring.

128
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:27,700
It isn't Luna's.

129
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:30,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

130
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:31,600
It's-- It's Mom's.

131
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:33,867
It's hers.

132
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,100
[EXCLAIMS] Bro!

133
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,133
- Cheska.
- I missed you!

134
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,733
Wow. You said 'Cheska'

135
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:43,300
as if you didn't know me.

136
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:45,100
Hey! What's up!

137
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:46,800
Cheska, what are you doing here?

138
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,967
What's wrong?

139
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,767
Hey! Goodness.

140
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:56,500
- Excuse me.
- Sorry.

141
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,233
Jade.

142
00:05:58,367 --> 00:05:59,533
Jade, wait.

143
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,567
Ahh.

144
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,800
So she's Jade.

145
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:06,600
Okay.

146
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:08,200
She's pretty. Great, great.

147
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:10,100
What are you doing here?

148
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,433
Why? Did I disturbing anything?

149
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:16,033
Was she about to say yes?

150
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,933
Whatever, Francheska.

151
00:06:18,067 --> 00:06:20,533
I'm not courting her.
Why would she say yes?

152
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:22,067
You tell me.

153
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:25,233
You seem so mad.
Who knows where that was going.

154
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:27,567
Why are you really here?

155
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:34,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:39,000
Why didn't you tell me
you were coming?

157
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:41,700
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:46,300
Mama and I wanted
to help you.

159
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:51,200
We had a family meeting
and we agreed...

160
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:54,000
that I will go here.

161
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,933
A family meeting?
Why wasn't I included?

162
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:59,400
And majority wins,
so you can't complain.

163
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,933
Hey, I'm doing you a favor.

164
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:04,367
Come to think of it.
I'll help you out here.

165
00:07:04,367 --> 00:07:08,100
You don't need to give me
money or pay me.

166
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:11,000
You just have to feed me
and let me stay here

167
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,333
- ...for a few days.
- Exactly how many days?

168
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:16,833
Bro, I don't like your tone.

169
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:18,833
Don't you want me here?

170
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:24,300
[CHESKA] Honestly, it hurts
my feelings.

171
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:27,733
I'm upset, but I can just
go home.

172
00:07:27,733 --> 00:07:29,333
- It's just one boat ride away.
- No.

173
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,767
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, okay?

174
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:34,267
You know, if you weren't
my sister,

175
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:37,200
I would've hit you for coming
at the wrong time.

176
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:42,167
Oh, my timing is wrong.

177
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:45,167
So, how are things going, bro?

178
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:47,100
Have you confessed your
feelings?

179
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:49,400
Are you taking your relationship
to the next level?

180
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,933
You're being pesky. Stop it.

181
00:07:51,933 --> 00:07:54,300
- Just shut it, Cheska.
- Someone's being cranky.

182
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,433
Come on, I'll introduce you
to my brothers.

183
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:57,733
Crankypants!

184
00:07:57,733 --> 00:08:00,067
Nice meeting you, Gio!

185
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:02,167
This is nice.
Feel at home, okay?

186
00:08:02,167 --> 00:08:04,133
There are many activities
you can do here.

187
00:08:04,133 --> 00:08:06,733
Just order any food
you want.

188
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:08,100
Hey. That's--

189
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,400
Kiko and I will take
care of it.

190
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,833
Would you look at that?

191
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:13,367
It seems Gio is nicer
than you, bro.

192
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:16,333
- Is that so?
- [CHUCKLES] I'm just kidding.

193
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:22,033
[CHESKA] You know what?
I'm still not used to this.

194
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:23,100
What do you mean?

195
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:26,800
You see, he's the eldest child
in our house,

196
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,400
but here, he's the youngest.

197
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,767
- Aww, you're the baby boy here.
- [KIKO SCOFFS]

198
00:08:30,767 --> 00:08:32,833
You know, you talk a lot.

199
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,367
[MARTIN] Gio. Kiko.

200
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,467
Hello.

201
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:41,900
- You again?
- Are you stalking me?

202
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,333
You know,
this hotel is huge.

203
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,367
We can choose not to
see each other.

204
00:08:47,367 --> 00:08:49,067
You two know each other?

205
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:52,000
- Uh...No.
- No.

206
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:55,033
- I'm Gio.
- Trixie. Hello.

207
00:08:55,067 --> 00:08:57,333
Uh... This is Trixie, my sister.

208
00:08:57,333 --> 00:08:58,800
- Hi.
- Oh.

209
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,167
- Your sister?
- Mm-hmm.

210
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:01,500
This is my sister, Cheska.

211
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,133
- I'm Martin.
- Hi, Martin.

212
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,767
You acted like
a VIP guest earlier.

213
00:09:05,767 --> 00:09:08,100
It turns out you're the sister
of Martin's brother.

214
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:10,433
[CHESKA] So what? It's true.

215
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:11,767
Right, Kiko?

216
00:09:11,767 --> 00:09:13,833
I'm a VIP
in my brother's life.

217
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:18,433
You should go to your
rooms and rest.

218
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,067
- Let's check in.
- Yeah, go.

219
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:23,400
- See you brother. Bye.
- You got it. Bye.

220
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:26,100
- Bye, Gio!
- Look at them.

221
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,067
Bye, Martin!

222
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:29,133
Gio, Martin...

223
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,033
We need to talk about
something.

224
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:36,533
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:39,000
I told you I'd deal
with Jade, remember?

226
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,500
Well? Did you find out
anything?

227
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:44,067
Yes, but it's still not clear.

228
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:45,767
What do you mean?

229
00:09:46,433 --> 00:09:49,333
She said the earring
doesn't belong to Luna.

230
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,833
It's Aunt Frida's.

231
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,867
So that means
Luna lied.

232
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:59,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

233
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:00,367
I don't know.

234
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:02,800
That's all Jade told me.

235
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:04,567
Did you find out
anything else?

236
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:06,233
No, I didn't.

237
00:10:06,233 --> 00:10:08,400
Cheska came so our conversation
was cut short.

238
00:10:10,033 --> 00:10:11,167
[MARTIN] Wait.

239
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:14,167
Aunt Frida was the only
one not with us

240
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,933
when we arrived
at the crime scene.

241
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:19,833
The four siblings were all
with us.

242
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:25,800
Could Aunt Frida have something
to do with Papa's death?

243
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:32,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:35,167
I guess now we can report this
to the cops.

245
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,067
But we're still not sure.

246
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:39,567
How can we be sure if we
don't tell them?

247
00:10:39,567 --> 00:10:41,167
Gio's right, Kiko.

248
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:42,933
It's no longer in our hands.

249
00:10:48,267 --> 00:10:52,267
Kiko found the earring
at the place where Papa died,

250
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:55,000
but Jade found out
and took it.

251
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:57,167
You gave it to her?

252
00:10:58,233 --> 00:10:59,633
Huh?

253
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:02,900
She said it belongs
to them.

254
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:06,267
She took it,
and I didn't get it back.

255
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:07,200
[GIO] Not only that, sir.

256
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,167
When the Almazans
returned to the hotel,

257
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,100
Luna claimed it was hers,

258
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:14,400
and she lost it when she
last visited her father.

259
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,933
That's possible.

260
00:11:18,067 --> 00:11:19,400
Sir.

261
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:22,667
But Jade herself said
that Luna is lying.

262
00:11:22,667 --> 00:11:26,033
The earring really belongs
to their mother.

263
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:28,100
It was Mrs. Almazan's?

264
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,933
Her daughter confirmed it?

265
00:11:29,933 --> 00:11:36,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:40,567
S-- Sir, isn't this an
important lead?

267
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:43,167
It might help solve
Papa's case.

268
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:50,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:11:55,533 --> 00:12:02,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:07,433
Slowly.
That's it, we're close.

271
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:09,767
- Ma, what are we doing?
- [LAUGHS]

272
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:11,233
Alright!

273
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:13,867
- Do I take it off?
- Yes, take it off.

274
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:14,833
[GRUNTS]

275
00:12:14,867 --> 00:12:16,967
[ALL] Surprise!

276
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:18,500
- Surprise, Justin!
- Happy birthday!

277
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,367
Happy birthday, Justin.

278
00:12:20,367 --> 00:12:24,267
[LUNA WHIMPERING] Aw!

279
00:12:25,533 --> 00:12:27,867
Sorry, I forgot.

280
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:29,900
You know your sister
has so much to think

281
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:31,167
about the hotel, right?

282
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,167
[PLEASANT MUSIC PLAYING]

283
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:35,167
Happy Birthday, Justin!

284
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:36,567
Even if...

285
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:39,200
We're always fighting.
[CHUCKLING]

286
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,067
You know I love you, don't you?

287
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:42,367
- [BOTH LAUGHING]
- Aw.

288
00:12:42,933 --> 00:12:44,333
Wow!

289
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:46,367
It's been a while since we all
hanged out like this.

290
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:49,467
[FRIDA] And we should do this
more often.

291
00:12:50,133 --> 00:12:52,467
You're all growing up so fast.

292
00:12:52,467 --> 00:12:56,233
I don't know for how long
I'll still be able to do this.

293
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,833
For me to be with you all.

294
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,167
I thought you...

295
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:01,333
Forgot it was today.

296
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:03,633
[FRIDA] No way.

297
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:05,333
That's never going to happen.

298
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:08,900
Do you remember when
your father was still alive?

299
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:12,367
No matter how busy he was,
no matter how moody he was,

300
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:15,533
when one of us
is celebrating their birthday,

301
00:13:15,533 --> 00:13:18,167
we have to be complete
no matter what.

302
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:23,400
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

303
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:24,567
Here.

304
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:26,900
- Time to blow your cake!
- [LUNA APPLAUDS]

305
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,467
- [JUSTIN CHUCKLES]
- [LIGHTER CLICKING]

306
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:29,667
- Not working?
- Uh-oh.

307
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:31,533
[JADE] Make a wish, Justin!

308
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:32,600
It's too windy.

309
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,967
Just imagine that the candles
are lit.

310
00:13:34,967 --> 00:13:36,433
- [JUSTIN SIGHS]
- [JADE LAUGHING]

311
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:38,300
- [FRIDA] Wish! Wish!
- Make a wish, Justin!

312
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:39,633
Alright. [CLEARS THROAT]

313
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,533
[BLOWS]

314
00:13:43,533 --> 00:13:45,233
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

315
00:13:45,233 --> 00:13:47,433
- What did you wish for, Justin?
- Thank you! It's a secret!

316
00:13:47,433 --> 00:13:48,500
- What was it?
- You'll know soon.

317
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,500
- More women!
- More women?!

318
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,633
- Uh-uh! Nope!
- That's what I want!

319
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:55,167
My wish is for you
to finally have a girlfriend!

320
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,267
- [LAUGHTER]
- Who could it be?

321
00:13:57,267 --> 00:14:03,167
[ALL SINGING HAPPY BIRTHDAY]

322
00:14:03,167 --> 00:14:05,433
[JADE] Dance, Justin! Let's go!

323
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:07,300
[SIGHS] Do you think
they'll do something

324
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:08,433
about what we reported?

325
00:14:09,567 --> 00:14:11,267
They have to.

326
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,567
It's their job.

327
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,367
[BOTTLE HISSING, POPS]

328
00:14:17,167 --> 00:14:20,233
Kiko, let me just remind you,
we're talking about Papa.

329
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:22,367
Don't you want justice
for him too?

330
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:24,433
I do but it might just cause
more tension

331
00:14:24,433 --> 00:14:26,400
between our family
and the Almazan's.

332
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,600
But we're doing this
not just for Papa,

333
00:14:29,633 --> 00:14:31,300
but also for their dad too.

334
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,133
[KIKO SIGHS]

335
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:38,300
Hey! Take a little break.

336
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:39,700
We brought snacks!

337
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:42,367
Oh, right. You guys disappeared.
Where did you all go?

338
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,033
Just hanging out.

339
00:14:44,667 --> 00:14:46,300
- Let's eat!
- Perfect timing!

340
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:47,467
- I'm hungry!
- Yes!

341
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:49,667
Eat up, guys!

342
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:50,933
- Eat up!
<i> - Palabok!</i>

343
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:54,100
Ms. Trixie, are you here
for the music festival?

344
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:56,267
Yes, of course!
Wouldn't miss it for the world.

345
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:59,200
It's my brother's first event
here so I can't miss it.

346
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,633
Also, I heard that there are

347
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:03,067
a lot of business
opportunities here, so...

348
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:05,267
I'm hitting two birds
with one stone.

349
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:06,767
What about me?

350
00:15:06,767 --> 00:15:08,300
Dude, I can help.

351
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:09,733
You can hire me as a staff!

352
00:15:10,367 --> 00:15:13,033
Oh, perfect! We need a staff!

353
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:14,667
- Right, Sir Gio?
- Exactly.

354
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,533
I can help too.

355
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,967
Are you sure?

356
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,267
Don't you want
to relax while you're here?

357
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:23,600
Huh? When did I ever rest?

358
00:15:24,167 --> 00:15:26,100
I want to help. Count me in.

359
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:30,300
Alright, let's all eat!

360
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:32,233
- [CHESKA] Aw!
- [TRIXIE] Aw!

361
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:34,733
Aw, Sis, did you miss me?

362
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,733
Well, our sirs all missed
their sister too.

363
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:41,033
How could I miss you
when we're together everyday?

364
00:15:41,033 --> 00:15:44,433
I'm just happy
because you're all complete!

365
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,433
And because of that...

366
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:47,667
Let's take a picture!

367
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:49,433
- Come on!
- Let's take a picture!

368
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:51,333
We rarely do this. Come on!

369
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:52,533
- Martin!
- Sir Martin, come on!

370
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,533
Don't be a killjoy, join us!

371
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:58,733
- Okay. One, two, three, smile!
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

372
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:01,033
[RAPHIE] It got quiet
all of a sudden. [CHUCKLES]

373
00:16:01,033 --> 00:16:02,200
Alright, one more!

374
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:05,100
- One, two, three, smile!
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

375
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:06,033
- Alright!
- That's enough.

376
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:08,100
- Yes. Go help yourselves!
- Thank you!

377
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,733
[MONETTE] The food's
gonna get cold.

378
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:11,100
[RAPHIE] I'm going
to post this, okay?

379
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,667
- [LAUGHTER]
- What's this?

380
00:16:12,667 --> 00:16:14,467
Eat more, Justin!

381
00:16:14,467 --> 00:16:15,633
- The pasta's good!
- Mmm!

382
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:19,333
- Leon, want some dip?
- Delicious! This is so good.

383
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:21,300
Mom, did you make the pasta?

384
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:22,600
No, it's from my favorite--

385
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,633
[WOMAN] The nerve to celebrate
when you just lost someone...

386
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:32,433
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

387
00:16:35,533 --> 00:16:36,567
[FRIDA EXHALES DEEPLY]

388
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:40,800
- Roi! Roi!
- [ROI] Yes, Ma'am?

389
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,267
Please take a picture
of us family.

390
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:44,300
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Okay.

391
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,100
- One, two, three!
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

392
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,767
- Wait, wait!
- Roi, include the entire table!

393
00:16:48,767 --> 00:16:50,367
Include the background too!

394
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:52,700
One, two, three!

395
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,500
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

396
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,767
Let's take one more.

397
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,400
[ROI CLEARS THROAT]

398
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,233
One, two...

399
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:04,333
[ALL] Happy Birthday, Justin!

400
00:17:05,533 --> 00:17:07,433
- Okay, come on.
- Thank you.

401
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:08,833
Can I see? Thank you.

402
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:10,867
- It's so hot!
- Let me see!

403
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:13,267
Wow, it's gorgeous.
It's beautiful!

404
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:14,400
Wow!

405
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,800
Aw!

406
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,633
[CHUCKLES]

407
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:19,867
I hope your dad could see this.

408
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:22,600
I'm sure he could see us, Mom.

409
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:28,833
[TOUCHING MUSIC]

410
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:30,800
Hello?

411
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:33,167
[INAUDIBLE]

412
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:34,800
Huh?

413
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,233
Dela Paz.

414
00:17:38,233 --> 00:17:40,100
Okay, I'll
call you later.

415
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:42,133
Where are you going?

416
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:45,833
Karma will get
those Almazans someday.

417
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:49,233
I'm sure they're behind
what happened to me.

418
00:17:49,733 --> 00:17:51,533
They want me to stop
going after them.

419
00:17:51,933 --> 00:17:53,533
Well they've made a mistake.

420
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:56,500
The dash cam footage,

421
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:59,333
the earring, it's enough
for them to get questioned.

422
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:01,867
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

423
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:03,200
I'll come with you.

424
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:06,133
[CAR DOORS OPENING]

425
00:18:08,433 --> 00:18:10,200
[CAR DOORS CLOSING]

426
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,867
Justin, you're the most
troublesome,

427
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:13,200
right, Mom?

428
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:15,633
- He's the most annoying!
- [LAUGHING]

429
00:18:15,633 --> 00:18:17,533
- How mean!
- No comment! [CHUCKLING]

430
00:18:17,533 --> 00:18:19,300
- [INAUDIBLE]
- Right?

431
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,833
True. Remember during
my birthday?

432
00:18:21,867 --> 00:18:23,667
It's my birthday but you're not
present. Why?

433
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,400
- Where were you?
- Sorry, I'm sorry.

434
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:28,300
He was following his teacher
that he used to have a crush on.

435
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:30,333
- [LAUGHING]
- Am I wrong?

436
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:31,933
It's why you had
high grades, isn't it?

437
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,167
Yeah.

438
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:35,233
Well, no. I mean...

439
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:38,233
What's going on?

440
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:39,200
Sir Henri.

441
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:40,767
What's going on?

442
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:43,400
We just want to invite
Mrs. Almazan

443
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,600
to the police station.

444
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:47,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

445
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:49,800
Why? What for?

446
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:52,267
For the case
of Michael Fernandez

447
00:18:52,267 --> 00:18:53,600
and Federico Almazan.

448
00:18:53,600 --> 00:19:00,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

449
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:12,833
We'd just like to invite
Mrs. Almazan to the station.

450
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:15,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

451
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:17,333
Why? What for?

452
00:19:17,867 --> 00:19:20,833
It's about the case of Michael
Fernandez and Federico Almazan.

453
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,300
Where's your warrant?

454
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,400
[MARINA] We don't have it but--

455
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,700
[LEON] Then she won't come
with you to the station.

456
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:30,433
We just have a question,
Mr. Almazan.

457
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:32,000
[LUNA] Whatever it is that
you want to ask,

458
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,867
ask her here.

459
00:19:33,867 --> 00:19:35,400
[HENRI] Are you sure?

460
00:19:36,033 --> 00:19:37,800
Alright then.

461
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:40,300
Mrs. Almazan,
where were you

462
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:43,300
when Michael Fernandez
and Federico Almazan died?

463
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:48,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

464
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,800
What kind of question
is that?

465
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:53,500
Mrs. Almazan, is it hard
to answer my question?

466
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:58,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

467
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:01,667
Where were you
when your husband

468
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,400
and Michael Fernandez died?

469
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:08,500
Mom, don't answer that.

470
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:17,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

471
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:23,933
Did you have something to do
with their death, Mrs. Almazan?

472
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:30,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

473
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:40,367
Mrs. Almazan.

474
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:41,333
No.

475
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,867
You better leave.

476
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:47,500
You have no right
to accuse my mother.

477
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,000
We know about the earring.

478
00:20:54,000 --> 00:21:00,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

479
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:17,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

480
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:21,933
We know about the earring.

481
00:21:22,067 --> 00:21:26,567
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

482
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,067
I need my lawyer.

483
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:46,467
I'll only speak
in the presence of my lawyer.

484
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:50,700
You're not deaf, right?

485
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:53,133
You heard her.

486
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:55,133
She's not going to speak
with you.

487
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:57,800
You're asking nonsense.

488
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,733
This is ridiculous.

489
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:02,400
I'm begging you,
Please, just leave.

490
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,400
I'm watching your every move.

491
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:08,033
[SOCFFS]
Watch as much as you want.

492
00:22:08,167 --> 00:22:10,667
This is a family occasion.

493
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:12,367
I hope you respect that.

494
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:14,667
You may go.

495
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:17,267
Let's go.

496
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:25,233
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

497
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:47,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

498
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,267
<i>You want me to bring
them back to life</i>

499
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,633
<i> to answer all your questions?</i>

500
00:23:00,767 --> 00:23:03,500
<i>You should not hide anything
if Mom didn't do anything bad.</i>

501
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:06,667
It feels good to have the hotel
<i> just for us, even for a day.</i>

502
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:10,200
<i>It's fun, right?
No one's prying. Yes, Lord!</i>

503
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,767
We're the men of the house now.

504
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:13,600
<i> We should protect our family.</i>

505
00:23:13,733 --> 00:23:16,633
<i>We didn't meet up.
I did not avail your services.</i>

506
00:23:16,767 --> 00:23:18,767
You might scare our guests away.

507
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,200
Then I'll go to the crime scene.

508
00:23:21,333 --> 00:23:23,067
- What's Mrs. Almazan's motive?
<i> - Who is that?</i>

